WEBVTT

00:04.320 --> 00:06.561
<i>TOMMY: Oh, there's a woman.</i>

00:08.360 --> 00:09.361
Yeah.

00:10.800 --> 00:11.801
A woman.

00:14.000 --> 00:15.411
Who I love.

00:17.560 --> 00:19.005
And I got close.

00:30.520 --> 00:32.329
In the bleak midwinter...

00:37.400 --> 00:39.368
At some point in the near future,

00:39.440 --> 00:41.761
Mr Churchill will want to speak to you
in person.

00:42.560 --> 00:43.686
Mr Shelby,

00:45.040 --> 00:46.565
he has a job for you.

00:46.680 --> 00:48.125
(PANTING)

00:48.200 --> 00:49.440
We will be in touch.

01:09.960 --> 01:11.962
(THEME SONG PLAYING)

01:12.520 --> 01:13.521
(CHURCH BELLS CHIMING)

01:20.640 --> 01:22.529
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

01:24.200 --> 01:25.850
Oh, thank you.

01:38.840 --> 01:40.365
-(BABY CRYING)
- I'm going to take him.

01:48.800 --> 01:50.290
Some of us know the words.

02:19.480 --> 02:20.845
Trot on.

02:23.560 --> 02:27.929
<i>(SI</i> N <i>GIN G) # In the bleak mid-winter</i>

02:28.000 --> 02:32.528
<i># Frosty wind made moan</i>

02:32.600 --> 02:36.491
<i># Earth stood hard as iron</i>

02:36.560 --> 02:37.891
Trot on.

02:37.960 --> 02:39.610
<i># Water like a stone</i>

02:39.680 --> 02:40.681
Trot on.

02:42.640 --> 02:47.521
<i># Snow had fallen, snow on snow</i>

02:47.600 --> 02:51.446
<i># Snow on snow</i>

02:52.680 --> 02:57.368
<i># In the bleak mid-winter</i>

02:57.440 --> 03:01.650
<i># Long ago #</i>

03:11.120 --> 03:12.884
<i>(ORGAN PLAYS BRIDAL CHORUS)</i>

03:16.960 --> 03:20.009
Here come the fucking cavalry.
Late as usual.

04:06.240 --> 04:08.004
JEREMIAH: Dearly beloved.

04:08.080 --> 04:12.449
We are gathered here today
to join together in holy matrimony

04:12.960 --> 04:16.851
Thomas Michael Shelby
and Grace Helen Burgess.

04:29.120 --> 04:30.121
(1 N DISTIN CT)

04:35.400 --> 04:37.050
MAID: Those flowers need to go there.

04:42.120 --> 04:44.043
<i>JEREMIAH:
Do you, Thomas Michael Shelby,</i>

04:44.760 --> 04:47.889
take Grace Helen Burgess
to be your lawful wedded wife?

04:49.480 --> 04:50.561
TOMMY: <i>I</i> do-.

04:52.320 --> 04:54.527
Do you, Grace Helen Burgess,

04:54.600 --> 04:58.002
solemnly swear to love, honour,

04:58.080 --> 05:01.527
<i>and obey till death do you part?</i>

05:01.600 --> 05:02.647
G RACE: <i>I</i> do-.

05:02.720 --> 05:05.963
<i>JEREMIAH: I now pronounce you
husband and wife.</i>

05:13.400 --> 05:15.289
(ALL CHEERING)

05:33.840 --> 05:35.046
Get out of it!

05:35.120 --> 05:36.804
(ALL TALKING IN DISTINCTLY)

05:44.000 --> 05:46.526
- Go on, take the photograph!
-(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

06:01.280 --> 06:03.328
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

06:09.160 --> 06:10.161
Tommy.

06:12.320 --> 06:15.483
Arthur, get the bastards in the house.

06:15.560 --> 06:20.282
I will. I will.john! john-Boy!
Get 'em in the house, all of 'em.

06:23.040 --> 06:25.088
Go on, all of you! Back to the house!
Go on!

06:25.720 --> 06:27.449
(ALL CHEERING)

06:52.320 --> 06:54.243
(ALL CH EERING AND APPLAUDING)

07:04.720 --> 07:06.768
(ORCHESTRA PLAYING)

07:30.920 --> 07:34.242
All right, Pol. Tell the Lee girls
I've counted all the paintings.

07:34.320 --> 07:37.210
And, Pol, some people here
are not on the list.

07:39.640 --> 07:41.642
Curly, Charlie. Kitchen.

07:41.720 --> 07:43.688
- Time?
- Five minutes.

07:43.760 --> 07:46.730
Actually, we were told on the train
there'd be cocaine.

07:47.800 --> 07:50.371
Jeremiah,john-Boy, kitchen, let's go.

07:50.440 --> 07:53.171
I swear to God them fucking Cavalry boys
are asking for it.

07:53.240 --> 07:56.449
Uh, I was told to ask someone young.
Will there be cocaine?

07:56.520 --> 07:59.967
Sweetheart, I am young, informed
and, uh, very well-equipped.

08:00.040 --> 08:01.485
You chose your man wisely.

08:02.520 --> 08:04.329
Come on, kitchen now.

08:04.400 --> 08:06.289
Arthur, this lady
wants to play in the snow.

08:06.360 --> 08:08.886
No, no snow today. No snow today.

08:11.080 --> 08:12.730
<i>ARTHUR: Kitchen, come on.</i>

08:12.800 --> 08:14.564
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

08:16.520 --> 08:18.249
(ALL LAUGHING)

08:21.000 --> 08:23.162
I just wish Tommy was here.

08:39.880 --> 08:41.405
- Where are they?
-JOHNNY: I don't know, Tommy.

08:41.480 --> 08:42.811
- Arthur, john, where are they?
- I don't know.

08:42.880 --> 08:45.690
- I am telling you now, we got lost.
- Come on.

08:45.760 --> 08:48.525
You really need to do a map.

08:56.560 --> 08:59.040
Right, boys, you're all here.

09:01.760 --> 09:04.684
Today, this is my fucking wedding day.

09:04.760 --> 09:07.206
Yeah, and you said
there'd be no bloody uniforms.

09:07.280 --> 09:09.886
Nevertheless... Nevertheless,john...

09:09.960 --> 09:12.247
Despite the bad blood,

09:12.320 --> 09:14.129
I'll have none of it on my carpet.

09:14.200 --> 09:17.204
Now for Grace's sake,
nothing will go wrong.

09:17.280 --> 09:20.921
Those bastards out there are her family.

09:21.000 --> 09:25.403
And if you fuckers do anything
to embarrass her,

09:25.480 --> 09:30.964
your kin, your cousins, your horses,
your fucking kids, you do anything...

09:31.040 --> 09:32.724
-j0HN: Tom?
- To... What?

09:32.800 --> 09:33.801
What about snow?

09:34.360 --> 09:36.567
Yeah, their women are sports,
I'll say that...

09:36.640 --> 09:38.563
No. No. No.

09:39.880 --> 09:41.041
No cocaine.

09:42.280 --> 09:44.328
No cocaine. No sport.

09:44.400 --> 09:46.767
No telling fortunes. No racing.

09:46.840 --> 09:50.731
No fucking sucking petrol
out of their fucking cars.

09:52.320 --> 09:55.642
And, you, Charlie,
stop spinning yarns about me, eh?

09:55.720 --> 09:57.768
I'm just trying to sell you
to them, Tom.

09:59.400 --> 10:00.561
But the main thing is,

10:01.400 --> 10:02.765
you bunch of fuckers,

10:03.320 --> 10:06.164
despite the provocation
from the cavalry,

10:06.880 --> 10:08.086
no fighting.

10:09.280 --> 10:10.281
Oi!

10:11.880 --> 10:13.086
No fighting.

10:13.160 --> 10:14.286
No fucking fighting.

10:14.960 --> 10:15.961
No fighting.

10:16.920 --> 10:20.447
(SHOUTING) No fucking fighting!

10:22.200 --> 10:23.201
Good.

10:23.640 --> 10:25.881
- Get the fuck off me!
-(GLASS SHATFERS)

10:32.960 --> 10:34.291
You're needed downstairs.

10:34.520 --> 10:35.806
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

10:38.440 --> 10:40.124
Grace, you're needed downstairs.

10:40.200 --> 10:41.406
People are hungry.

10:42.240 --> 10:44.242
I was putting Charles to sleep. (SIGHS)

10:44.840 --> 10:46.842
I'll come down,
but not with you like this.

10:46.920 --> 10:48.046
All right, fine.

10:49.120 --> 10:50.281
GRACE: Tommy.

10:51.920 --> 10:56.084
I thought today was the reason
for the way you've been acting lately.

10:56.160 --> 10:58.447
I know there's business on your mind.

11:00.040 --> 11:02.088
- And I know there always will be.
- Yeah.

11:02.160 --> 11:04.640
Look, I am sorry
that they wore their uniforms.

11:04.720 --> 11:07.564
Yeah, they fucking did, eh.
They fucking did.

11:07.640 --> 11:09.324
But I can tell it's more than that.

11:11.680 --> 11:13.648
You've been like this for weeks.

11:15.880 --> 11:17.211
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

11:18.320 --> 11:20.561
I need you to tell me

11:21.320 --> 11:23.322
that it's business making you like this.

11:23.400 --> 11:25.323
And not regret over me.

11:26.560 --> 11:28.164
Say it out loud
and I'll know if it's true.

11:29.520 --> 11:30.851
(CLICKS TONGUE)

11:33.120 --> 11:34.565
It's business, Grace.

11:37.320 --> 11:39.448
And bad, bad business it is, all around.

11:45.120 --> 11:47.122
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

11:47.200 --> 11:48.850
And I'm scared, Grace.

11:50.240 --> 11:51.765
I'm scared for you.

11:51.840 --> 11:53.410
I'm scared for the baby.

11:53.840 --> 11:55.046
And this is how I am when I'm scared.

11:55.120 --> 11:57.248
It is unfamiliar to you, but not to me.

11:57.320 --> 12:02.167
I can... I can fucking be scared
and carry on.

12:06.240 --> 12:09.130
And it's not pleasant to look at
and no joy to be around.

12:10.800 --> 12:12.165
All right?

12:15.240 --> 12:17.402
I'm sorry. (SNIFFS)

12:24.360 --> 12:26.442
We just made vows to share everything.

12:28.840 --> 12:31.002
Tell me what it is you're afraid of.

12:41.080 --> 12:43.208
-(MUSIC PLAYING)
-(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

12:55.000 --> 12:57.207
Stand up. Stand up, stand up.

12:59.920 --> 13:01.081
Arthur's speech.

13:02.640 --> 13:04.324
I'm scared of fucking Arthur's speech.

13:07.800 --> 13:08.926
All right?

13:10.240 --> 13:11.571
Me, too.

13:15.240 --> 13:16.969
Tommy, what are you doing?

13:17.040 --> 13:18.087
Tommy.

13:18.160 --> 13:22.051
There's half the British Army
waiting for us downstairs.

13:22.560 --> 13:26.929
They're King's Irish.
We waited two weeks in the mud for them.

13:28.360 --> 13:30.488
Tommy. (GIGGLES)

13:32.240 --> 13:36.245
There are things, that if I take them
off, I won't be able to put back on...

13:36.320 --> 13:38.288
- That's good.
-(CHUCKLES)

13:45.600 --> 13:47.170
Hello, Mrs Shelby.

13:48.280 --> 13:51.204
- I'm sorry for being busy in my head.
-(CHUCKLES)

13:53.360 --> 13:55.203
Now let's complete the ceremony.

13:57.280 --> 13:59.169
Hey, listen. Listen, listen.

13:59.240 --> 14:02.562
What do you call an animal
with a prick halfway up its back?

14:03.280 --> 14:05.487
A cavalry horse. (LAUGHING)

14:06.240 --> 14:07.730
He got... He gets it.

14:10.440 --> 14:12.283
Fuck it. Fuck it.

14:12.360 --> 14:14.522
Where the bloody hell are they?
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

14:14.600 --> 14:17.410
You're best man, Arthur.
Go and find them.

14:19.320 --> 14:20.481
Yeah.

14:21.800 --> 14:23.290
ADA: That's completely nonsense.

14:23.360 --> 14:26.409
You know, we're part of a serious
political movement and organisation.

14:26.480 --> 14:29.802
They're not "secret little meetings,"
they're just meetings.

14:29.880 --> 14:32.008
We talk about the world,
about the people in it,

14:32.080 --> 14:34.970
about our current political landscape
and what's going on.

14:35.040 --> 14:37.088
You know, we really need to re-evaluate
the way our government...

14:37.160 --> 14:38.730
(WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)

14:41.040 --> 14:43.486
- POLLY: He's strange.
- He's looking over.

14:43.560 --> 14:44.561
What?

14:46.880 --> 14:48.848
He's coming. He bloody is.

14:50.880 --> 14:52.928
Fuck. It's the wrong one.

14:53.600 --> 14:55.284
What do you mean "the wrong one"?
How many are there?

14:55.360 --> 14:56.964
There's two, giving me the eye.

14:57.040 --> 14:59.008
I prefer the other one.
He looks harmless.

15:01.680 --> 15:04.604
It must be that bloody lipstick
Tommy brought you back from New York.

15:09.120 --> 15:11.691
I couldn't help noticing
you are unaccompanied.

15:11.760 --> 15:15.321
I also am alone. May I join you?

15:23.680 --> 15:26.206
ARTHUR: Tommy?
Oh. (SNIFFLES)

15:26.880 --> 15:30.646
Didn't see a thing. Did not see a thing.
Sorry, brother.

15:31.680 --> 15:33.125
I need you downstairs.

15:33.720 --> 15:35.210
It's all right. We're done. (SIGHS)

15:35.280 --> 15:36.486
- You good?
- Yeah.

15:36.560 --> 15:37.925
- Never been better.
- Yea h?

15:38.000 --> 15:39.604
- Are you drunk?
- Huh? No.

15:40.400 --> 15:41.401
No.

15:43.360 --> 15:44.361
Here.

15:47.720 --> 15:49.768
All right, it's just one drink, then.

15:50.280 --> 15:52.089
Linda's a good woman, Arthur.

15:56.720 --> 15:57.881
Good whisky.

15:59.400 --> 16:01.687
A good man needs to
hold out sometimes, eh?

16:07.000 --> 16:08.331
(SIGHS)

16:08.760 --> 16:13.209
So, uh, do I mention this
in my speech, then, eh?

16:13.280 --> 16:15.806
Not unless you want to get cut, Arthur.

16:15.880 --> 16:17.211
ARTHUR: Sorry, sister.

16:18.400 --> 16:19.811
TOMMY: Right. Look.

16:20.520 --> 16:22.488
Tell the maids
to break out the champagne.

16:22.560 --> 16:23.925
We'll be down in a minute.

16:24.000 --> 16:26.002
Champagne, yeah. OK.

16:26.840 --> 16:29.207
- I got it right here. I'm ready.
- Good. Good.

16:33.520 --> 16:35.090
Where are you from?

16:40.680 --> 16:41.727
I'm a refugee.

16:43.440 --> 16:44.441
From where?

16:50.000 --> 16:51.240
Russia.

16:53.480 --> 16:54.561
In the past few months,

16:54.640 --> 16:57.450
Thomas has developed
some business interests with Russia.

16:59.480 --> 17:01.528
I see he has confided in you.

17:03.920 --> 17:04.967
Hmm.

17:05.040 --> 17:07.566
You need his permission
to even speak to me.

17:11.200 --> 17:13.851
My senior position
within the Shelby company

17:13.920 --> 17:17.560
means I don't often have
to ask permission from anyone

17:17.640 --> 17:19.050
to do anything.

17:19.720 --> 17:21.483
So perhaps you'lljust tell me

17:21.560 --> 17:26.009
why the fuck you're talking Russian
business on Thomas's wedding day.

17:27.720 --> 17:30.121
LIZZIE: Hold on, wait a second. So
you're saying I'm not allowed a man...

17:30.200 --> 17:31.531
It's about your choice of man.

17:31.600 --> 17:32.761
LIZZIE: I'm not allowed a man on my arm?

17:32.840 --> 17:34.285
MICHAEL: Thomas says
that they're the rules.

17:34.360 --> 17:36.283
LIZZIE: Fucking parish bastard!

17:36.360 --> 17:38.761
Michael, speeches. Come on.

17:38.840 --> 17:41.684
Arthur. You know
why he didn't come, don't you?

17:41.760 --> 17:43.125
Why who didn't come?

17:43.200 --> 17:44.611
My bloody man.

17:44.680 --> 17:46.205
Oh, you mean the wop?

17:46.280 --> 17:50.490
LIZZIE: I just heard there was a fire
at his restaurant midnight last night.

17:50.560 --> 17:53.006
And a smashed back window
and a smell of petrol.

17:53.640 --> 17:56.211
Lizzie, we tried to talk some sense
into you.

17:56.720 --> 17:58.006
We did checks on him.

17:58.080 --> 18:00.003
He's had five different names
in the last six years,

18:00.080 --> 18:01.730
and he's got connections
with the Naples boys.

18:01.800 --> 18:02.801
ARTHUR: Come on, Michael.

18:02.880 --> 18:04.291
What do you know about love?

18:04.360 --> 18:06.169
About when lightning strikes.

18:06.240 --> 18:10.006
So, it was lightning, hmm? Not petrol.

18:11.080 --> 18:12.366
I thought you were
off the whisky, Arthur.

18:12.440 --> 18:14.886
Yeah, I am. Having a couple
now and again

18:14.960 --> 18:16.325
to remind myself why I don't drink it.

18:16.400 --> 18:17.447
(CHUCKLES)

18:17.520 --> 18:20.444
You set fire to his restaurant
to stop him coming.

18:20.520 --> 18:23.729
You have no right to choose
who I step out with in my own time!

18:28.440 --> 18:29.851
(MICHAEL CLEARS THROAT)

18:34.560 --> 18:39.487
Lizzie, you now have an important
position in this company.

18:40.560 --> 18:43.609
You got the order, same as us.

18:45.680 --> 18:47.409
You can do it.

18:52.120 --> 18:54.248
Until further notice...

18:55.280 --> 18:57.681
No fraternizing with the foreigners.

19:01.400 --> 19:02.925
Yeah, well, you can tell Tommy from me

19:03.000 --> 19:05.651
all the girls in the office think
he's losing his fucking mind!

19:11.360 --> 19:12.691
To the bride.

19:12.760 --> 19:13.966
ALL: The bride.

19:14.040 --> 19:15.485
- The bride.
- The bride.

19:18.280 --> 19:22.524
And now, (CLEARS THROAT)
according to tradition,

19:22.600 --> 19:25.001
my best man will say a few words.

19:25.200 --> 19:30.081
Go on! Here he goes! Go on, Arthur!

19:34.400 --> 19:37.609
I'd like to, erm...
I'm not one for speeches.

19:37.680 --> 19:39.921
- Sing, then!
- ARTHUR: I will later, john.

19:41.320 --> 19:43.926
But, er... I do, er...

19:44.920 --> 19:47.685
I do have some words written down here

19:49.560 --> 19:51.210
on this piece of paper.

19:52.520 --> 19:57.401
This doesn't include everything
that I want to say.

19:57.480 --> 19:59.608
Arthur,just, uh...
just read what we wrote down, eh?

20:00.800 --> 20:03.963
- I will. I will.
- Mmm-hmm.

20:04.040 --> 20:05.280
But...

20:06.320 --> 20:10.644
First... First, uh, a few words from...
From the heart.

20:14.480 --> 20:15.481
Um...

20:17.000 --> 20:19.651
This man here, my brother Tommy,

20:20.800 --> 20:25.010
helped me survive through
some of the worst times.

20:25.120 --> 20:26.724
(COUGHS AND CLEARS THROAT)

20:26.800 --> 20:28.882
It's a wedding, Arthur, tell a joke.

20:28.960 --> 20:30.121
JOHN: Yeah, tell a joke.

20:30.720 --> 20:33.041
What I am trying to say is that...

20:34.800 --> 20:39.362
(STUTTERS) My brother
and the love of a good woman

20:40.680 --> 20:42.842
pulled me through that time.

20:44.440 --> 20:48.525
Now Tommy also
has the love of a good woman.

20:50.080 --> 20:51.923
Her name's Grace.

20:53.480 --> 20:55.721
Like the grace of the good Lord.

20:58.680 --> 20:59.681
And even though

21:01.360 --> 21:05.684
the circumstances of their union
was tragic...

21:05.760 --> 21:08.047
All right. Let's, uh... Arthur.

21:08.120 --> 21:10.168
Let's raise a toast, eh?

21:10.240 --> 21:11.969
To, uh... (CLEARS THROAT)

21:12.040 --> 21:15.601
To love, to peace, to marriage.

21:15.680 --> 21:17.409
- And to marriage.
- To marriage.

21:23.240 --> 21:27.768
JOHN: Well done, Arthur,
beautiful speech. Really nice.

21:29.600 --> 21:30.886
Really, really nice.

21:37.840 --> 21:40.002
JOHN: Where is he fucking going?

21:44.640 --> 21:47.086
- I think I messed it up.
- No, not a bit.

21:47.480 --> 21:49.881
- Hmm.
- You spoke with such truth.

21:50.920 --> 21:52.410
And God heard you.

21:52.480 --> 21:54.130
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

21:55.320 --> 21:58.085
TOMMY: Can I have a word
with my brother, please, Linda?

21:58.640 --> 22:01.610
- What he was going to say was beautiful.
- Mmm-hmm.

22:02.320 --> 22:03.731
Alone, please.

22:09.560 --> 22:10.846
All right. Come here.

22:12.080 --> 22:13.127
Come here.

22:15.000 --> 22:16.490
(TOMMY SIGHS)

22:17.800 --> 22:19.802
We talked about this, Arthur.

22:19.880 --> 22:21.689
That's why we wrote it all down.

22:22.800 --> 22:26.691
Most of Grace's side don't even know
her husband killed himself.

22:26.760 --> 22:27.966
They think it was an accident.

22:28.960 --> 22:30.246
- Oh, I know.
- You know.

22:31.440 --> 22:32.646
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

22:32.720 --> 22:34.290
What do you think I am? Hmm?

22:35.880 --> 22:37.928
What do you think I am, Tommy, eh?

22:38.480 --> 22:41.450
- You think I'm a fucking idiot!
- All right, boys.

22:41.520 --> 22:44.683
- Come on, have a good night.
- You think I would say it...

22:44.760 --> 22:47.366
- Come on, then. That's it.
- You keep walking, you nosy bastards.

22:47.440 --> 22:50.091
- Arthur.
- You stay away from me.

22:50.160 --> 22:52.811
- Fuckin hell.
- You stay away from me. I've had enough.

22:55.440 --> 22:56.441
Ah!

22:56.800 --> 22:57.847
Shit.

22:58.360 --> 23:00.249
-(GROANING)
- Yeah. Yeah.

23:04.920 --> 23:06.684
(ARTHUR GROANS)

23:09.280 --> 23:10.725
Ah, shit.

23:12.560 --> 23:15.040
Three shots I've had. That's it.

23:15.120 --> 23:16.770
- TOMMY: I know.
- I drew the line.

23:16.840 --> 23:17.887
I know.

